<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <p xml:id="PN367-intro">tiṇai, pāṭāṇṭiṇai; tuṟai vāḻttiyal. cēramāṉmāveṇkōvum pāṇṭiyaṉ kāṉappērtanta ukkirapperuvaḻutiyum cōḻaṉ irācacūyamvēṭṭa perunaṟkiḷḷiyum oruṅkiruntārai auvaiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PN367">
<l>nākat taṉṉa pākār maṇṭilan</l>
<l>tamavē yāyiṉun tam<supplied>moṭu cellā</supplied></l>
<l>vēṟṟō rāyiṉu nōṟṟōrk koḻiyu</l>
<l>mēṟṟa pārppārk kīrṅkai niṟaiyap</l>
<l>pūvum poṉṉum puṉalpaṭac corintu</l>
<l>pāciḻai makaḷir polaṅkalat tēntiya</l>
<l>nārari tēṟaṉ <supplied>mānti</supplied> makiḻ<supplied>ciṟan</supplied></l>
<l>tiravalark karuṅkala marukātu vīci</l>
<l>vāḻtal vēṇṭumivaṇ varainta vaikal</l>
<l>vāḻac ceyta nalviṉai yalla</l>
<l>tāḻuṅ kālaip puṇaipiṟi tillai</l>
<l>yoṉṟupurin taṭaṅkiya virupiṟap pāḷar</l>
<l>muttīp puraiyak kāṇṭaka virunta</l>
<l>koṟṟa veṇkuṭaik koṭittēr vēntir</l>
<l>yāṉaṟi yaḷavaiyō vituvē vāṉattu</l>
<l>vayaṅkit tōṉṟu mīṉiṉu mimmeṉa</l>
<l>viyaṅku māmaḻai yuṟaiyiṉu</l>
<l>muyarntumēn tōṉṟip polikanun nāḷē.</l>
</lg>
<lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Although the orb full of fates, like [that of] the snakes,</l>
<l>was their’s, it did not go with them. (1f.)</l>
<l corresp="3">Although they were different ones, it stayed behind for those who were toiling. </l>
<l corresp="9">It is necessary to live, in the days here that are limited, </l>
<l corresp="8">showering without stinting precious ornaments to mendicants, </l>
<l corresp="7">exulting in delight, drinking toddy filtered through fibres </l>
<l corresp="6">that is offered from golden vessels by women with green[-golden] jewels, </l>
<l corresp="5">pouring so that flowers and gold fall in a flood </l>
<l corresp="4">to fill the moist hands of the receiving brahmins. </l>
<l corresp="10">Apart from the good deeds performed while living </l>
<l corresp="11">there is no other support at the time one sinks. </l>
<l corresp="14">You kings with bannered chariots [and] victorious white parasols </l>
<l corresp="13">who sit, fit to be seen, like the three fires </l>
<l corresp="12">of the men with two births who desire [and] retain one thing, </l>
<l corresp="15a-c">as far as I know it is this. </l>
<l corresp="18">May your days of appearing on top be more numerous </l>
<l corresp="17">than the drops from dark clouds that move </l>
<l>noisily, more than the flashes of lightning that appear glowing in the sky. (15df.)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
